By: Marty Kowal |  Jan 12, 2016



I have an AT&T card with 20% interest. I tryed to get the CITIBANK simplicity card to transfer the balance but they won't do it!


Reply



Thank you. Your comment has been submitted and is pending editorial review.




  Submit Comment




1 Reply





By: CompareCards | Jan 12, 2016
Hi Marty,

It is a rule in the credit card industry that you cannot transfer balances between credit cards issued from the same bank. The reason you are not able to transfer your balance to the Citi Simplicity is because the AT&T Access More Credit Card is issued by Citibank as well. But 20% APR is very high, so I would certainly recommend transferring your balance to a low interest credit card to avoid paying a fortune in interest. Two cards to consider that aren't issued by Citibank would be the Chase Slate, which offers 15 months with 0% APR and no balance transfer fee, or the Discover It, which has 18 months with 0% APR.










